  "text": "It has been shown that npr1 mutants exhibit decreased expression of the PR1 gene, which is defined as a senescence and pathogen-defence associated gene, after SA treatment [CITATION_1] . Therefore, we speculated that NPR1 might participate in exogenous SA-induced leaf senescence. To explore the function of NPR1 in leaf senescence, typical physiological markers of senescence were examined in detached leaves of WT and npr1 mutants.",
